annotation.TEXT: This hack gets an "A"! Also, I need to press "A" to spin jump off these L'il Sparkies, obviously. This would be pretty tricky even without the L/R switching going on here, so... Yeah, it's plenty tricky.
BGM: Seiken Densetsu 3 - Harvest November
Oh, man. I see the trickiness coming up ahead here!
Here's some pencils, but they should be no problem to avoid if I'm careful.

Whoa, another "zwee", and now the clock over my Yoshi coin counter is doin' stuff! Alright, here's how this part works... Every time that clock hits zero, the direction I'm allowed to move changes, then the clock starts over from 3 again. This is gonna get interesting...
Wow, okay! It fires diagonal bullets that luckily didn't hit me there!
Huh, looks like another Yoshi filter, so I'm glad I didn't bring him this time. Also, I can't move left or even face that way. But, what happens if I hit an ON/OFF block?
Made it! Now I guess I have to do the same with a running jump. ...Uh, oh. I'm getting low on time here. I hope the goal isn't too far away!
I so want to hit that ? block behind me, but that's not happening, at least until I hit an ON/OFF block that's to my right.
Agh! That wasn't quite the right L/R timing for me there...
Oh, there's another cape, but I have to be able to move left to reach it. Oh, man. What's with the red skull and crossbones box?
Got my reserve cape! Oh, please let the goal be just ahead!
Cool, a cape! I wonder if I can use a cape spin to hit that ON/OFF block there without having to worry about the pencil...
It looks like the yellow coins hint at the Podoboo locations, but I think one of the Podoboos failed to spawn due to the sprite limit.
Other than that, it plays the same. Make complete horizontal lines to score points, and... Umm...
Oh, man. This looks like it'll be a tricky Yoshi coin to reach.
Ah, now I can move left, but I can't move or face right.
More diagonal Podoboo dodging.
Hey, gimme my mushroom! ...Well, that's no problem. If I hit this ON/OFF block here, I can go over and get it!
Ah, I definitely want that Yoshi coin, but... Will the L/R switching timing be cooperative enough for me to get it without getting smashed by the Thwomp?
NO!!! ...Wait, I'm not dead yet! Maybe I can come back from this!
Alright, looks like it's time for the final vote of this hack! Where should I go next? :P :P :P, or Vanilla Secret Yu? (Or an endless bonus game level?)
Aha! Spin jumping at that time worked!
...Huh... I see a problem here. There's no place for this Z piece to land. How am I supposed to create complete lines if I can't set any pieces down anywhere?
Ow, my jumping feet! Well, so much for the cape...
Now to go up here and hopefully not get stupidly sawed in half.
Hmm... Getting past Thwomps could get surprisingly tricky if the timing of the L/R switching isn't good.
Oh! But it worked anyway! Okay, so cape spins will still work in both directions.
Place your votes now, and we'll find out the order that I'll play these levels next time! To be continued... :P
Looks like spin jumping still works, although it appears that Mario will never face the illegal direction even while spinning.
And, let's begin! Okay, so the game has started me off with the Z piece (aka squiggly), and I have a line piece coming up next.
Vanilla Secret Yu

The L/R timing tried to be uncooperative there, but I noticed that that cement block was just 5 tiles up from that turn block bridge's horizontal state, so I didn't have to wait for it to become vertical during "L" time!
Yeah, I figured flight was disabled here. Huh, it looks like I've gotta time my bounce here so that I'm in the right spot in midair as it switches from "R" to "L".
Heh, I can't even slide backwards!
Fortunately, the L/R gimmick of the level doesn't carry over into the bonus game, so I can move normally here.

YES!!! Whew! I made it at the very last second there! ...Yeah, the timer says 2, but the L/R clock was at 1 when I hit the goal, and if it had switched on me again before I hit the goal, my rightward movement would've been halted, and I would've died from time up for sure!
I guess the coins are hints as to how the turn block bridges will act. This last one here can stretch vertically.
Ah, I see what I need to do here.
Bonus game average so far: 9 / 2 = 4.5 1-ups each.
And why is that bullet cannon a slightly different color? ...Oh, because it's a Missile Bill shooter, like the one I saw in the :) level last episode.
Looks like screen scrolling with L and R still works, which is cool.
That L'il Sparky isn't much of a threat to me.
Oh, man. Hammer Brother platform that dips into the lava. The level's getting trickier.
I really don't want to have to rush this part, but I have so little time left. However, if I screw up and fall into the water below, I'll almost certainly time out!
Alright, halfway done. I'm guess I'd emerge from that yellow pipe if I needed to restart this level from midpoint.
Being able to whack that Dry Bones certainly helps. Alright, let me guess... There's a hidden coin block here, right? ...Yep!
Umm... I don't know. Since I can't face right, the cape doesn't ever appear on my left while I'm spinning.
I'll certainly take that extra cape!
I am so glad I had a cape, which seemed to work perfectly with the L/R switching timing! And it looks like this hack gets another "A"! Also, I'll gladly take another cape!
BGM: Donkey Kong Country Returns - Fear Factory Returns
Alright, now with this switch pressed, I can go left, but not right. Of course, I can still press right to slow/stop my leftward movement.

Okay, now this level begins for real. I'm sure that I'll want to go up the left side, but I'm forced to go to the right across the lava here right now. These jumps are gonna be tricky due to the movement restriction.
Good. I was worried that that last pair of Podoboos would screw me over. Oh, there's the last Yoshi coin. I'd better make sure to get it!
I guess I just drop down here.
And now, another normal speed bonus game! (I refuse to go to ludicrous speed until I've perfected at least one bonus game in this hack.)

If you look at the top of the screen near the timer, you'll see either an R or an L, which shows which direction I'm currently allowed to move. Huh... I wonder what that clock symbol with a 3 next to it on the left is for? Well, let's not worry about that right now.
I have to keep in mind that I can't move left at all. However, I can still press left to slow/stop my rightward movement.
Fortunately, that spin jump bouncing went well. Now for diagonal Podoboos in water. I can pass through the S-blocks, but the Podoboos can't.
Goal tape average so far: 205 / 9 = 22.778 stars each.
I don't think I'll be trying for every coin here.
Turn block bridges shouldn't be much of a problem if I just aim for the center of the bridges.
Huh, that's weird. Now a couple of the other Podoboos aren't resurfacing. Well, that makes my life a little easier.
Alright, I'm glad I didn't miss hitting it!
Wow, there were a ton of votes this time!
So, this game plays just like regular Tetris, except that when a piece falls through the portal at the bottom of the playing field, it reappears up top.
There's some more Missile Bill shooters. Now, it looks like I have to take the lower path here first, which had some Podoboos that I need to watch out for.
Come on! Let me move right!
:P :P :P

(Oh, even worse, I just noticed that the player could get totally trapped by falling to the floor while moving left and going down that passage to the left again, because there's no ON/OFF block in that lower-left corner to allow the player to escape! That's a level design flaw for sure!)
We've got Maverick Thwomps here, and they can pass through the M-blocks, which are solid for me.
Alright! Now if I do happen to time out or die some other way, at least I won't have to worry about getting all of the Yoshi coins again.
There's one. Aim carefully...
Alright, let's play Portal Tetris! Here's a quick look at the simple controls...
Endless bonus game (LOL)
Hello, and welcome back to Three Spitting Emoticons, or ":Px3" for short! Alright, now let's take a look at the voting results here...
Well, this is kind of an exercise in futility then. I'm outta here.
No, I did not want to hit that ON/OFF block an extra time there.
Bounce off a bullet to hit the switch above, and repeat a couple more times. Try not to fall, or you'll have to repeat the Podoboo section if you were moving right.
Whoops. I should've capitalized this "c".
Nuts, just missed it there.
Perfect! Time for some victory dive bombs!
